// HumanityOS ship structure: MANY pressurized zones, each a fixed outer box + freely
// placed interior walls (the proven home model, now plural -- increments A + B of
// docs/design/ship-superstructure.md). Each zone: id, label, purpose
// (residence|commons|bay|agriculture|corridor), a world origin for its box min corner
// (y = deck height), and the full home body in zone-local metres. The former
// data/blueprints/home_structure.ron migrated outright into zone 'home' below.
// `corridors` (bottom of the file) generates straight walk-through tubes between
// two zones' door openings -- see the comment there for the row shape.
//
// AI + human friendly: add a zone by adding an entry to zones; add a wall by adding an
// InteriorWall line inside a zone body. The construction editor edits the same data
// (zone selector at the top of the Home structure panel).
//
// Materials: 0 = grid, 1 = steel/metal, 2 = concrete, 3 = wood, 4 = glass.

